{{Infobox film awards | number = 27 | award = Bangladesh National Film Awards | image = | alt = | caption = | awarded_for = Best of Bangladeshi cinema in 2002 | award_org = [[President of Bangladesh]] | presenting_org = [[Ministry of Information (Bangladesh)|Ministry of Information]] | announced_date = | presented_date = 2004 | site = [[Dhaka]], Bangladesh | host = | website = [http://www.moi.gov.bd/ Official website] | best_feature = ''[[Hason Raja (2002 film)|Hason Raja]]'' | best_non_feature = | best_actor = [[Kazi Maruf]] | best_actor_film = ''[[Itihash]]'' | best_actress = Not Given | best_actress_film = | most_wins = ''[[Hason Raja (2002 film)|Hason Raja]]'' (7) | last = 26th | next = 28th }}
The '''27th National Film Awards''', presented by Ministry of Information, Bangladesh to felicitate the best of Bangladeshi Cinema released in the year 2002. Bangladesh National Film Awards is a film award ceremony in Bangladesh established in 1975 by Government of Bangladesh. Every year, a national panel appointed by the government selects the winning entry, and the award ceremony is held in Dhaka.<ref name=bdnews24>{{cite news|url=http://glitz.bdnews24.com/details.php?catry=2&showns=2012 |title=চার দশকে আমাদের সেরা চলচ্চিত্রগুলো |date= |work=bdnews24 |author=Rashed Shaon |accessdate=November 4, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127231625/http://glitz.bdnews24.com/details.php?catry=2&showns=2012 |archivedate=January 27, 2013 |df= }}</ref> An eleven-member jury board chaired by the additional secretary of the Ministry of Information selected the winners in different categories.<ref name=thedailystar>{{cite news|title=National Film Awards for the last fours years announced|newspaper=The Daily Star|date=2008-09-01|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/newDesign/story.php?nid=52684|accessdate=October 12, 2015}}</ref> A 12-member jury board headed by Sadeq Khan, Chairman of Board of Directors, Press Institute of Bangladesh suggested the name of 17 artistes for the National Film Award in recognition of their outstanding contributions to the country's film industry.<ref>{{cite news|title=National film awards for 2002 and 2003 declared|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2004/11/24/d411241402105.htm|newspaper=The Daily Star|date=2004-11-24|accessdate=October 13, 2015}}</ref>
==List of winners== A Total of 17 awards were given in this year.
