'''Aaron Crow''', also known as '''The Silent Mentalist''', '''The Warrior''' or '''Mystical''', is a [[Belgian]] [[Mentalism|mentalist]], [[stage magician|magician]] and [[Swordsmanship|danger-act]], known for his appearances on "Le Plus Grand Cabaret Du Monde", [[Britain's Got Talent]] and [[America's Got Talent]].

Crow is known for adopting a strong, silent stage persona.  He was featured in The Sydney Opera House and on Broadway New York with two of his signature acts in the biggest touring magic show in the world "The Illusionist" , alongside fellow magicians as  [[Dan Sperry]], [[Kevin James (magician)|Kevin James]] and Jeff Hobson. In 2016, he premiered his full evening show "FearLess" in Malaysia.

== Early life ==
Crow's official website states: "At the age of three, Aaron was rushed to hospital with a needle stuck in his throat. It was a frightening experience, although luckily he made a complete recovery."

At the age of five, Aaron was startled when a mouse crawled on his back while he was in bed. "Aaron says it made him think about how people overcome their fears – and that the key is to confront them."<ref name= "BGT">{{cite news |last1= Watts |first1= Halina |last2= Hill |first2= Patrick |title= ''Britain's Got Talent'' 2013: Silent mentalist Aaron wants to throw knife at Simon Cowell |location= London |publisher= ''[[Daily Mirror]]'' |date= Apr 28, 2013 |url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/britains-talent-2013-silent-mentalist-1857924 |accessdate= September 15, 2014}}</ref>

On his twelfth birthday, Aaron's parents gave him a book about the legendary Harry Houdini. From the book, Aaron learned that Houdini – the greatest showman of his era – used to perform a famous routine in which he swallowed many sharp needles."<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.aaroncrow.com/en/pages/1/early-days |author= Crow, Aaron |date= |title= Early Days |publisher= www.aaroncrow.com |accessdate= September 15, 2014}}</ref>

== Career ==
He won first place ''Mental Magic'' at the "[[Fédération Internationale des Sociétés Magiques#Convention|World Championships of Magic]]"<ref>FISM – The Book, Ghiurmino, Aldo, W. Meister & Co. Editori, {{ISBN|9788890607424}}, page 268}</ref>  and since then multiple highly coveted awards like "Le Mandraque d'or" in Paris.

He has performed on numerous television shows around the world, but is mainly known for his appearances on ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]'', during which he performed a blind-folded [[swordsmanship]] act, in 2013. {{Citation needed |date=September 2014}} 

Crow auditioned for the [[Britain's Got Talent (series 7)|seventh series]] of ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]''. His audition aired on 27 April 2013.

Crow led two audience members and host [[Anthony McPartlin|Ant McPartlin]] onstage. He gave the woman a bag to hold, the man a board to hold upright, and McPartlin a pineapple to hold on top of his head. Next, Crow poured hot candle wax over his eyes and covered his face with bandages, black tape and foil. He then used a Knife to slice the bag, nunchucks to break the board, and a [[Katana]] to slice the pineapple in half – all with deadly precision of course.{{Citation needed |date=September 2014}}

''The Daily Mirror'' reported, "A ''BGT'' insider said: 'Aaron's performance went down a storm with the judges and viewers'."<ref name="BGT" /> [[Simon Cowell]] stated "That's a great act. I love the idea of watching something where there is a possibility that someone could actually die, and the fact that it was Ant made it more exciting."<ref>{{cite news |author=  |title= Britain's Got Talent 2013: Ant McPartlin fears for his life as 'mentalist' Aaron Crow takes to the stage |work= [[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |location= [[Kensington]], [[London]] |publisher= [[DMG Media]] |date= 27 Apr 2013 |url= http://metro.co.uk/2013/04/27/britains-got-talent-2013-ant-mcpartlin-fears-for-his-life-as-mentalist-aaron-crow-takes-to-the-stage-3668187/ |accessdate= September 15, 2014}}</ref> The other judges also praised the performance. [[Alesha Dixon]] added, "I find you really intriguing. Just the way you commanded the stage and your presence alone was exciting. It was dangerous, I was like oh this is great and you were just fantastic. Loved it." [[Amanda Holden]] stated, "My heart was like pumping through my ribcage. The suspense and the intrigue and the mystery, it was absolutely terrifyingly brilliant."{{Citation needed |date=September 2014}}

On 27 May 2013, Crow returned for the semi-finals, during which he shot an apple sitting on host [[Declan Donnelly]]'s head.<ref>{{cite news |author= Dave   |title= Aaron Crow Channels William Tell in ''Britain's Got Talent'' Semi-Final (Video) |work= Daily Picks and Flicks |date= 2013-05-27 |url= http://dailypicksandflicks.com/2013/05/27/aaron-crow-channels-william-tell-in-britains-got-talent-semi-final-video/ |accessdate= September 15, 2014}}</ref> He finished fourth.

Since then Aaron Crow has been traveling the world with the bestselling magic show in the world "[[The Illusionists]]".  He performed in The Sydney Opera House and started an eight-month tour in the US with four week on Broadway New York where the show was a major hit.

In 2016, Crow focused on his own full evening show called FearLess!   The show premiered in Genting Malaysia.

He competed on the [[America's Got Talent (season 13)|thirteenth season]] of [[America's Got Talent]] in 2018.  He was eliminated in the semi-finals. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espeakers.com/s/grbl/profile/32098|title=eSpeakers Marketplace|website=www.espeakers.com}}</ref>

In October 2018 his show "Mystica" was one of the main Halloween attractions at [[Walibi Belgium]] <ref>{{cite tweet|title=https://twitter.com/ItsAaronCrow/status/1054314111000023040|author=AARON CROW|user=ItsAaronCrow|number=1054314111000023040|date=2018-10-22}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Aaron Crow has a science degree and was a teacher in a juvenile institution for many years, where he eventually became head of campus.{{Citation needed|date=January 2018}}

He has earned a [[Black belt (martial arts)|black belt]] in [[Taekwondo]].<ref name="BGT" /> and was for a short while part of the National Belgian Tae Kwon Do team.

