'''Fantastic Television Limited''' ({{Lang-zh|奇妙電視}}) is a commercial [[free-to-air]] television broadcasting company in [[Hong Kong]] owned by [[I-Cable Communications]]. Fantastic Television draws resources and programming libraries from the fellow I-Cable company, [[Hong Kong Cable Television]] (Cable TV).

Established in 2009, the company's [[broadcast licence]] was granted by the Hong Kong Government on 31 May 2016. The company operates two channels: Cantonese [[Hong Kong Open TV]] since 14 May 2017, and English [[Hong Kong International Business Channel]] (HKIBC) since 30 July 2018.

As of 2018, Fantastic Television's channels are broadcast through Cable TV's network, and not available on terrestrial television.

==Channels==
* [[Hong Kong Open TV]] (channel 77): Formerly named Fantastic Television Channel 77
* [[Hong Kong International Business Channel]] (channel 76): The channel was tentatively named Fantastic TV English Channel, but after [[Forever Top (Asia) Limited|Forever Top]]'s acquisition of Fantastic Television's parent company I-Cable Communications in 2017, it was later announced in early June 2018 that the channel would be launched as an English and Putonghua business channel named HKIBC. The channel simulcasts [[Bloomberg Television]] for most of the day, but also relays [[CGTN (TV channel)|CGTN]] in the mornings from 7 am to 9 am. The channel produces English language news bulletins which are aired in the evenings<!--Unlike ViuTVsix whose English bulletins are produced externally by Reuters-->, and also airs non-business and obligatory programmes as mandated in the licence.

==External links==
* {{Official website|http://www.hkopentv.com/}}
* [http://www.hkibchannel.com.hk/index_eng.html Hong Kong International Business Channel]

